Description: tuneteams is a music business marketplace, an auctions platform for B2B music licensing and a free music industry professional network.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: tuneteams' mission is to help music companies build international businesses because in a fast-changing music industry, at least one thing is clear - there are more music stores selling legal music in more countries than ever before. Getting music to stores around the world is easy thanks to the internet and a handful of great digital distribution companies that have developed over the last 20 years. But having music on stores around the world is useless unless local music fans know it's there, and hiring local marketing people around the world is expensive. Luckily, the music industry has long had a solution for that - revenue-sharing deals called recording licenses or sub-publishing deals. But finding partners and negotiating deals for multiple album releases across multiple countries is difficult for all but the biggest labels and publishers. That's where tuneteams comes in.  They've created an online service to make this process easier in the following ways. tuneteams provides a platform where music companies can present their releases to the international music industry. Record labels and publishers can search for available music to license by country, genre and rights type (e.g. recording, publishing, or sub-publishing). tuneteams' auction process facilitates negotiating licenses for multiple releases across multiple countries. tuneteams provides template recording license, publishing and sub-publishing contracts to make it easy for music companies of all sizes and experience levels to easily create partnerships. And tuneteams provides money transfer and escrow services so companies can feel safe that they will get paid and/or only pay if they receive the music, artwork, etc. Some people say they're "eBay for music licensing meets LinkedIn for the music biz." Some people call all that an online marketplace for music licensing. They call it making it easier for the international music industry to work together.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Community and Lifestyle, Content and Publishing, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio, Professional Services

As a client, you need a lawyer that you are comfortable with, an attorney who knows the Texas judicial system, and the clerks, prosecutors, judges, and courts in Fort Worth, Dallas, and other jurisdictions across our state. If you’re charged with a crime, you need an attorney you can rely on to provide aggressive and effective criminal defense representation. Dallas defense attorney Gary Medlin and the legal team at The Medlin Law Firm can provide the candid answers you need, and they will explain the options available for your defense. We prepare every case with the presumption that the case may go to trial. We let the prosecution know that winning a conviction against you may not be easy. And as your case unfolds, we will keep you fully informed of any plea bargaining or reduced sentencing options that may be available to you. With more than 36 years as a Texas criminal defense attorney, Gary Medlin has represented thousands of clients. His background as a prosecutor in both federal and state courts means that he knows the law from both sides of the courtroom, giving his clients a considerable advantage.

Description: TapMetrics is a tool from iPhone app developers that brings sales data, user feedback, software metrics, and other information together.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: TapMetrics is a tool designed by a team of iPhone application developers that brings together sales data, user feedback, software metrics, and other information into a consolidated dashboard to allow developers to manage a portfolio of applications quickly and easily. The whole experience starts with a dashboard that lets you view important information about how your application portfolio is performing, and then lets you drill into each application to investigate any issue that is highlighted.  The nice part of the TapMetrics solution is that while it does a great job on the business metrics of running an iPhone application, it does just as good of a job serving the needs of the engineer.   Everything from detailed environmental data (which iPhone/Touch hardware is being used, which OS level, which release level of the application), to detailed crash reporting, to application messaging/event logs, and session tracking are supported within the integrated TapMetrics experience.   They also have a free Mac OS X app called TapMini that you can use to automatically download sales data for your iPhone applications.  If you are trying to get more out of your iPhone application portfolio (both in terms of improving the consumer experience and making more revenue), this can be a really useful tool.

Description: IYIA has been conducting an IRB approved study using O2Misly™ on chronic diabetic foot ulcer patients at two clinics in southern California.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Approximately 2.4 million diabetic foot ulcers are diagnosed each year in the U.S, many progressing to lower limb amputation. It is estimated that the U.S. healthcare costs for treating diabetic foot ulcers and related amputations exceed $10 billion per year. Treating diabetic foot ulcers that have continually failed standard care therapies is a frustrating problem. IYIA Technologies, Inc. has been developing and testing a treatment therapy system, O2Misly™, which actually heals these, failed wounds. IYIA has been conducting an IRB approved study using O2Misly™ on chronic diabetic foot ulcer patients at two clinics in southern California. O2Misly™ technology is a new method, a medical device that offers a combination, adjunctive therapy to the standard of care. O2Misly™ provides oxygen infused under micro tension in a closed chamber blended with a mist, which also delivers an antimicrobial to the affected area. O2Misly™ technology is producing remarkable results. Patients that had failed various standard of care therapies and have had open wounds for years are seeing their wounds finally heal. IYIA Technologies, Inc. is excited to bring the O2Misly™ Wound Treatment System to a patient population that has faced the consequences of a debilitating disease with little hope of winning their battle.

Description: The CrossPollinators is an open-source digital platform.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The xPollinators (pronounced “CrossPollinators”) exists to change the way the world connects to community organizations. Activists and changemakers are spending hours mapping out resources or reinventing the wheel. Their tool connects people working on regenerating their local communities to each other in order to share resources and knowledge, as we collectively build the world up. We are closing the gap between each other, so you don’t have to spend hours researching on Google or getting lost in Facebook. There are countless community efforts working on social good. But they are all stuck in disparate silos. This is the place for leaders to start connecting the dots to paint out a unified image of the movement: Individuals can be powerful cross-pollinators by using it as a tool to store and share their knowledge of their local community;  Organizations can use it as a community engagement portal to track and share resource map of relevant groups. Contributing to the xPollinators is like building a digital garden. The more the users share what they know in their own community, the more flourishing the garden becomes. Join us to co-create a digital garden of community-based solutions to breed more pollinators for their future. This is the place for citizens to get inspired to take action and team up to build resilient communities.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Data and Analytics, Government and Military, Information Technology, Internet Services, Navigation and Mapping, Software
